Notes on Type of testing – Unit and Integration testing

Updated by 25_Jay

System testing is the execution of the software in its final configuration, including integration with other software and hardware systems.

It tests for security, performance, resource loss,timing problems, and other issues that can’t be tested at lower levels of integration

It is a white box type testing

The acceptance testing plan is created during the design phase and the actual testing is done after the system is fully developed and tested.

Beta Testing is the equivalent of Acceptance testing as the final end-users who will buy the game are involved in the testing.

It is a black box type testing 

